The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Friday, January 03, 2003 				 Murder charge on BSF jawan
																								Krishnagar, Jan. 2: The BSF and Nadia police locked horns over yesterdays killing of two brothers near the border in Chapra police station area even as the frontier guards shot dead a Bangladeshi intruder in the same area today.																								The police have filed a case against the BSF jawans who shot Azamat and Nizamat Mondol after a third person allegedly snatched an assault rifle from a jawan and fled. Police sources said the case was an outcome of intense public resentment against the BSF. 																								A case has been started against the jawans under Section 302 of the IPC, that implicates a person in murder, said the districts additional superintendent of police, P.K. Ghosh.
